<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Agreed</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Wrex">Wrex</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 12:04 a.m. 17/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Agreed<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1512" TARGET=_self>Re: Factions</A> (Tarquin)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Phase 3 notified you of what factions were effected by what you killed. They took this out, and I agree that you shouldn't be able to see the math involved in the factions. It takes away from the game if you see that killing a Goblin will make you one point happier with the Dwarves.

<P>I do think that you should be able to choose one faction at time (perhaps once a week) and be able to see what your chosen faction thinks of killing a certain creature will do it. For example: The Aviac chick looks at you dubiously - You think you would have the upper hand - Dwarves think Aviacs are tasty like chicken.
<P>Another option would be NPCs say what creatures they are fond of and which are enemies. That should at least be a starting point.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
